<br>
ad3n, yes, that information helps a lot.  Did you read the second post in this thread?  If not, go back and read it carefully as it tells you exactly how to download and install the IME.  UglyWhiteKid has also summarized it nicely in the post above.<br>
At any rate, just to make it all absolutely positively crystal clear:<br>
1) Go to <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.microsoft.com/windows/ie/downloads/recommended/ime/install.asp" target="top">this link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Pull down the menu and select &quot;Microsoft Global IME 5.02 for Japanese - with Language Pack&quot;.  <br>
2) Download it.  Install it (if it doesn't automatically).<br>
3) Read the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>second</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> post in this thread.  Everything should make sense.  Follow the instructions word for word.<br>
<br>
4) As has been mentioned, you'll need to be in a program that supports japanese.  Internet Explorer will work nicely.  Click on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.yahoo.co.jp" target="top">www.yahoo.co.jp</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  Under the &quot;View&quot; menu, go to &quot;Encoding&quot; and select &quot;Japanese-Auto Select&quot;.  You should see japanese on your screen.<br>
5) You can type Japanese.  Click on the blue EN in the bottom right corner of your screen (Read the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>first</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> post in this thread if you can't find it).  Select &quot;JP&quot;.  Change your input to Japanese (read the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>second</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> post if you don't know which is the correct item to select).  <br>
6) Put your cursor in the search engine field, then type japanese. ta-dah! <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sit.wisc.edu/~mamiller2/panda/panda3.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
